We’ve seen Mother Nature at her worst; now we’re seeing Wilmington at its best. As the healing process begins, you can find WPD exactly where we were before and during the storm — right by your side, because together we are #ILMStrong.

We’ve seen the best the Port City has to offer. People from all over the country are working to undo the damage Florence has inflicted upon us, and we are grateful. But no one is working harder than your city crews.

Rumors have swirled, patience is thin, and tensions are high, but we have seen far more good. We’ve seen friends extend a helping hand to those in need. We’ve seen neighbors open their homes to those who are stranded. We have seen a recovery effort focused on community.

The past few days have seemed like years, and we know we’re not the only ones who feel like that. Since last week, the City of Wilmington, NC has been ravaged. Parts of our city are underwater, parts are without power and some parts are inaccessible.pic.twitter.com/g3HvkWhXnY
